The United States has condemned the attack on the United Nations compound in Herat, Afghanistan. The attack resulted in the death of an Afghan guard. The United Nations in Afghanistan is a civilian entity that supports peace efforts, promotes the rights of all Afghans, and provides humanitarian and development assistance. Attacks against civilian UN personnel and facilities are prohibited under international law. The United States is calling for an immediate reduction in violence in Afghanistan and for regional actors to encourage the parties to return to negotiations without delay. The goal is to achieve a durable and just political settlement that brings peace and security to the Afghan people.